Brazilian Stock Movers: LLX Logistica, Natura, QGEP Advance

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-08-24T20:44:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/brazilian-stock-movers-llx-logistica-natura-qgep-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index was little changed at 53,795.70.  LLX Logistica SA (LLXL3)  (LLXL3 BS), the port developer controlled
by Brazilian billionaire  Eike Batista , increased 5.6 percent to
3.78 reais. Ferrovia Centro Atlantica SA said it signed a
memorandum of understanding to develop a feasibility study for a
railroad in Rio de Janeiro state for LLX, according to a
regulatory filing.  Natura Cosmeticos SA (NATU3)  (NATU3 BS) gained 1.5 percent to 37.65
reais.  Brazil ’s biggest cosmetics maker was raised to
“neutral” from “underperform” at Credit Suisse Group AG.  QGEP Participacoes SA (QGEP3 BS) climbed 1.2 percent to
15.48 reais. The  oil company  controlled by Queiroz Galvao SA
agreed to buy part of Shell Brasil Petroleo Ltda.’s stake in the
BS-4 block in Brazil’s  Santos Basin , according to a regulatory
filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  